@wu-sheng Probably I am misinterpreting the code. And it is already working correctly.
I thought that https://github.com/apache/skywalking/pull/9914/files#diff-7c42c99e33896647d67385263076ec5178df8e57d072e760895ed7ca9f5d1c20R219-R223
is always applied, and that `config.getIndexShardsNumber()` already contains either the default value or the override.

Which version are you talking about? I am feeling this had been fixed by https://github.com/apache/skywalking-java/pull/290 months ago.

```
notify(GRPCChannelStatus.CONNECTED);
reconnectCount = 0;
reconnect = true;
```

This is not going to be the execution order anymore.

> 你说的是哪个版本？我觉得这已经被[apache/skywalking-java#290](https://github.com/apache/skywalking-java/pull/290)个月前修复了。
> 
> ```
> notify(GRPCChannelStatus.CONNECTED);
> reconnectCount = 0;
> reconnect = true;
> ```
> 
> 这将不再是执行顺序。

V9.2.0

@terrymanu @tristaZero This test case should be able to help you locate the compatibility issue we faced in the integration.
Once the ITShardingTest could pass on your new release, I think it would be easy for us to bring more compatible versions of ShardingSphere into our e2e testing.

Also, we tried to use ShardingSphere to provide a PostgreSQL cluster option, but fail due to the DistSQL doesn't work as expected and as before.

@kezhenxu94 @wankai123 ElasticSearch and Sharding ITs take a lots of time, should we consider separating them in the CI?
More ElasticSearch versions could be tests, and sharding pg is on our roadmap too.

Is this possible?
